cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper proposes a novel sequence-to-vector embedding method for text classification, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency and neural network-based solutions, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and preserving sequential structure, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper mentions experimental results with dense networks, which could also indicate a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
